Now Sadony the kinges Sonne, whose only contentment was in the company of Blanchardine, day by day inuented new sportes, and quainte deuices, to exhillerate and make him mery. But Blanchardine, calling to mind the extreamity of his most sweet Lady Eglantine, the Quéene of Tormaday, by reason of the long and daungerous seidge of King Alimodes, could not be d •…
lighted with any nouelties. And in this extasie let vs leaue him (but in the high fauor of the king and his Sonne Sadon •…
) and returne we to tell of the King of Frize Father to Blanchardine.
